# Per-agent launchd config consumed by render.sh.
#
# Format: each non-comment, non-blank line is a record with up to six
# tab-separated fields:
#
#   1. label       - launchd job label (also the .plist filename stem)
#   2. script      - python file in ALFRED_HOME/bin/ to invoke
#   3. schedule    - one of:
#                      interval:<seconds>
#                      cron:<HH>:<MM>                 (daily)
#                      cron:<weekday>:<HH>:<MM>       (weekly; 0=Sun)
#   4. needs_java  - "yes" or "no". "yes" prepends openjdk@21 + fnm
#                    bins to PATH and sets JAVA_HOME. Set this for any
#                    agent whose claude -p might compile Kotlin or invoke
#                    Node tooling that fnm pins.
#   5. log_stem    - basename used for /tmp/<stem>.{stdout,stderr}.
#                    Empty falls back to label. Useful when two plists
#                    share a script (sso-check-10 and sso-check-22 both
#                    write to /tmp/my.fleet.sso-check.{stdout,stderr}).
#   6. role        - one-line operational descriptor in plain English.
#                    Surfaced in `alfred agents` and Slack post prefixes;
#                    codenames alone don't
#                    carry meaning to a fresh contributor (or to your
#                    future self at 2am). Keep it under ~50 chars.
#                    Optional but strongly recommended.
#
# Tabs are required between fields. Trailing empty fields can be omitted.

# Example entries. Replace with your own codenames.
#
# A scheduler-style codename that polls every 20 minutes:
#   my.fleet.poller	poller.py	interval:1200	yes			Issue poller
#
# A nightly reviewer that runs at 02:00:
#   my.fleet.reviewer	reviewer.py	cron:2:00	yes			Nightly PR reviewer
#
# A weekly Sunday-night dependency scanner at 22:00:
#   my.fleet.deps	deps-scanner.py	cron:0:22:00	yes			Weekly dependency audit
#
# A check that fires at 10:00 AND 22:00 (two rows, shared script + log_stem):
#   my.fleet.health-am	health-check.py	cron:10:00	no	my.fleet.health	Fleet health (morning)
#   my.fleet.health-pm	health-check.py	cron:22:00	no	my.fleet.health	Fleet health (evening)
#
# Opt-in: damian, the spec-bundle planner. Uncomment after configuring
# DAMIAN_SCAN_REPOS and DAMIAN_SPEC_DIR, then `alfred enable damian`.
# Fires once a day; matches the daily-bundle cap baked into the runner.
#   my.fleet.damian	damian.py	cron:9:00	no		Spec-bundle planner
#
# Opt-in: scheduled memory harvest. Queues reviewable candidates from repeated
# failure patterns, posts only when there is something to review, and never
# promotes lessons by itself.
#   my.fleet.memory-harvest	memory-harvest.py	cron:8:05	no		Memory candidate harvester
#
# Opt-in: gated memory auto-promotion. Promotes ONLY high-confidence,
# evidence-backed, judge-approved candidates into recall, capped per run, and
# leaves everything else for the human review queue. Stays a true no-op until
# ALFRED_AUTO_PROMOTE=1 arms it; ALFRED_AUTO_PROMOTE_KILL=1 halts it without
# editing config. Run after the harvest so freshly queued candidates are seen.
#   my.fleet.memory-auto-promote	memory-auto-promote.py	cron:8:20	no		Gated memory auto-promoter

# Anonymous usage totals. This line stays commented until an install configures
# an endpoint. The script sends only aggregate counts to ALFRED_TELEMETRY_URL,
# and ALFRED_TELEMETRY_ENABLED=0 opts out. No repo names, code, prompts, titles,
# branches, people, or hostnames are sent.
#   my.fleet.proof-telemetry	proof-telemetry.py	interval:3600	no		Anonymous usage totals
